1504 |label=[[Club Am\u00e9rica (women)|Am\u00e9rica]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Greater Mexico City |lat=19.3313 |long= -99.1925 |label=[[Club Universidad Nacional (women)|UNAM]] |position=top}}\n}}\n\n===Personnel and kits===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n! Team\n! Chairman\n! Head Coach\n! Kit manufacturer\n! Shirt sponsor(s)\n|-\n|Am\u00e9rica\n| [[Santiago Ba\u00f1os]]\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Leonardo Cu\u00e9llar]]\n| [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]]\n| [[Huawei]]\n|-\n|Atlas\n| Pedro Portilla\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Fernando Samayoa]]\n| [[Adidas]]\n| MoPlay\n|-\n|Atl\u00e9tico San Luis\n| Alberto Marrero\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Luis Arnaldo Mart\u00ednez|Luis Mart\u00ednez]]\n| [[Pirma]]\n| [[Canel's]]\n|-\n|Cruz Azul\n| Guillermo \u00c1lvarez Cuevas\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Rogelio Mart\u00ednez Morales|Rogelio Mart\u00ednez]]\n| [[Joma]]\n| [[Cemento Cruz Azul]]\n|-\n|Guadalajara\n| Amaury Vergara\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Ram\u00f3n Villa Zevallos]] \n| [[Puma (brand)|Puma]]\n| Sello Rojo\n|-\n|Ju\u00e1rez\n| [[Guillermo Cant\u00fa]]\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Gabino Ampar\u00e1n]]\n| Carrara \n| Del R\u00edo\n|-\n|Le\u00f3n\n| Jes\u00fas Mart\u00ednez Murguia\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Everaldo Begines]]\n| [[Pirma]]\n| Cementos Fortaleza\n|-\n|Monterrey\n| [[Duilio Davino]]\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[H\u00e9ctor Becerra]]\n| [[Puma (brand)|Puma]]\n| [[AT&T]]\n|-\n|Morelia\n| Mauricio Lanz Gonz\u00e1lez\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Filadelfo Rangel]]\n| [[Pirma]]\n| [[Kansas City Southern de M\u00e9xico]]\n|-\n|Necaxa\n| Ernesto Tinajero Flores\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Fabiola Vargas]]\n| [[:es:Charly (marca)|Charly]]\n| Rolcar\n|-\n|Pachuca\n| Jes\u00fas Mart\u00ednez Pati\u00f1o\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Eva Espejo]]\n| [[:es:Charly (marca)|Charly]]\n| Cementos Fortaleza\n|-\n|Puebla\n| Manuel Jim\u00e9nez Garc\u00eda\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Jorge Isaac G\u00f3mez|Jorge G\u00f3mez]]\n| [[Umbro]]\n| [[AT&T]]\n|-\n|Quer\u00e9taro\n| Rodrigo Ares de Parga\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[F\u00e9lix Mart\u00ednez Mendoza|F\u00e9lix Mart\u00ednez]]\n| [[Puma (brand)|Puma]]\n| Banco Multiva\n|-\n|Santos Laguna\n| Dante Elizalde\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez Padr\u00f3n]]\n| [[:es:Charly (marca)|Charly]]\n| [[Soriana]]\n|-\n|Tijuana\n| Jorge Hank Inzunsa\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Carla Rossi]]\n| [[:es:Charly (marca)|Charly]]\n| Caliente\n|-\n|Toluca\n| Francisco Suinaga\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Agust\u00edn Contreras]]\n| [[Under Armour]]\n| [[Banamex]]\n|-\n|UANL\n| Miguel \u00c1ngel Garza\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Roberto Medina]]\n| [[Adidas]]\n| [[Cemex]]\n|-\n|UNAM\n| Leopoldo Silva Guti\u00e9rrez\n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Ileana D\u00e1vila]]\n| [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]]\n| [[DHL Express]]\n|}\n\n==Format==\n*The Liga MX Femenil season is split into two championships: the [[#Torneo Apertura|Torneo Apertura]] (opening tournament) and the [[#Torneo Clausura|Torneo Clausura]] (closing tournament). Each is contested in an identical format and includes the same nineteen teams. <ref name=\"LigaMXFemenil\">http://administrador.ligamx.net/docs/Reglamentos/Competencia/8_LIGA_MX_FEMENIL/06_LIGA_MX_FEMENIL_1_20180723175320.pdf</ref>\n\n*Since 2019\u201320 season the teams compete in a single group, the best eight of the general table are classified to the championship playoffs.<ref name=\"ASM\u00e9xico\">{{cite web |last1=Mancilla |first1=Sergio |title=Los cambios m\u00e1s relevantes de la Liga MX Femenil para el AP19 |url=https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2019/07/10/futbol/1562762218_180224.html |website=As.com M\u00e9xico |accessdate=12 July 2019 |language=Spanish |date=10 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Changes===\n*Due to the addition of Atl\u00e9tico San Luis, this season will consist of nineteen teams, for that reason, the groups were eliminated.<ref name=\"LMFMT\" />\n*Lobos BUAP were bought by FC Ju\u00e1rez, Ju\u00e1rez acquired all the BUAP's obligations including have a women team.<ref name=\"ESPN\">{{cite web |last1=Marshall |first1=Tom |title=FC Juarez buys Lobos BUAP, takes spot in Liga MX |url=http://www.espnfc.mx/liga-bbva-bancomer/story/3873555/fc-juarez-buys-lobos-buap-takes-spot-in-liga-mx |website=ESPN |accessdate=12 July 2019 |date=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n*This season will consist of 19 rounds (up from 17).<ref name=\"Calendario\">{{cite web |title=Calendario del Torneo Apertura 2019 |url=https://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/detallenoticia/30590/calendario-del-torneo-apertura-2019 |website=Liga MX Femenil |accessdate=12 July 2019 |date=25 June 2019}}</ref>\n*One team will rest each round.<ref name=\"Calendario\" />\n\n==== Mid-season changes ====\n* [[Tiburones Rojos de Veracruz Femenil|Veracruz]] will not participate in the Clausura 2020 due to the dessafiliation of the [[Tiburones Rojos de Veracruz|main team]].<ref> http://ligamx.net/cancha/detallenoticia/32956/se-revoca-certificado-de-afiliacion-al-club-tiburones-rojos-de-veracruz</ref>\n\n==Torneo Apertura==\nThe Apertura 2019 season began on 12 July 2019 ended in December 2019.\n\n===Regular Season===\n\n====Standings====\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|start_date=12 July 2019\n|source=[https://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/tablas/tablaGeneralClasificacion/sp/120303357672f1 Liga MX Femenil]\n\n<!--Update team positions here-->\n|team1=MON|team2=UNL|team3=PAC|team4=AME|team5=GUA|team6=TOL|team7=TIJ|team8=ATL|team9=MOR|team10=CAZ|team11=LEO|team12=PUE|team13=QUE|team14=UNM|team15=VER|team16=SAN|team17=ASL|team18=JUA|team19=NEC\n\n<!--Update team qualifications here (defined below)-->\n|result1=LIG|result2=LIG|result3=LIG|result4=LIG|result5=LIG|result6=LIG|result7=LIG|result8=LIG\n\n<!--Update team results here and then (if needed) positions above. Don't forget to update the date (update parameter).-->\n|update=11 November 2019\n|win_AME=9 |draw_AME=5 |loss_AME=4 |gf_AME=29 |ga_AME=17 <!-- Am\u00e9rica -->\n|win_ATL=7 |draw_ATL=7 |loss_ATL=4 |gf_ATL=35 |ga_ATL=20 <!-- Atlas -->\n|win_ASL=2 |draw_ASL=5 |loss_ASL=11 |gf_ASL=11 |ga_ASL=38 <!-- Atl\u00e9tico 