na||311\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\nSource: [http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/asistencia Liga MX Femenil]\n\n=== Liguilla ===\nThe eight best teams play two games against each other on a home-and-away basis. The higher seeded teams play on their home field during the second leg. The winner of each match up is determined by [[Two-legged tie#Tiebreaking|aggregate score]]. In the quarterfinals and semifinals, if the two teams are tied on aggregate and on [[Away goals rule|away goals]], the higher seeded team advances.<ref>per Liga MX Femenil online 'reglamentos' 2019/2020 (QF and SF) - \"De existir empate en el n\u00famero de goles, la posici\u00f3n se definir\u00e1 a favor del Club que haya anotado una mayor cantidad de goles actuando como visitante.\"</ref> In the final, if the two teams are tied after both legs, the match goes to extra time and, if necessary, a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]].\n\n{{8TeamBracket-2Leg \n| RD1=[[#Quarter-finals|Quarter-finals]]\n| RD2=[[#Semi-finals|Semi-finals]]\n| RD3=[[#Final|Final]]\n| group1=\n| group2=\n| group3=\n\n| seed-width=\n| team-width=\n| game-score-width=\n| agg-score-width=\n\n| RD1-seed01=1\n| RD1-team01='''[[C.F. Monterrey (women)|Monterrey]]\n| RD1-score01-1=0\n| RD1-score01-2=1\n| RD1-score01-agg='''1\n| RD1-seed02=8\n| RD1-team02=[[Club Atlas (women)|Atlas]]\n| RD1-score02-1=0\n| RD1-score02-2=0\n| RD1-score02-agg='''0\n| RD1-seed03=4\n| RD1-team03='''[[Club Am\u00e9rica (women)|Am\u00e9rica]]\n| RD1-score03-1=2\n| RD1-score03-2=1\n| RD1-score03-agg='''3\n| RD1-seed04=5\n| RD1-team04=[[C.D. Guadalajara (women)|Guadalajara]]\n| RD1-score04-1=0\n| RD1-score04-2=0\n| RD1-score04-agg='''0\n| RD1-seed05=2\n| RD1-team05='''[[Tigres UANL (women)|UANL]]\n| RD1-score05-1=0\n| RD1-score05-2=3\n| RD1-score05-agg='''3\n| RD1-seed06=7\n| RD1-team06=[[Club Tijuana (women)|Tijuana]]\n| RD1-score06-1=0\n| RD1-score06-2=0\n| RD1-score06-agg='''0\n| RD1-seed07=3\n| RD1-team07='''[[C.F. Pachuca (women)|Pach