porters assistance due to precautionary measures against the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]}} ||UNAM||0\u20130||Cruz Azul||22,289||Quer\u00e9taro||0\u20133||Morelia||260\n|-\n|11{{efn|name=Midweek|Round scheduled for midweek.}} ||||||||||||||||\n|-\n|12 ||||||||||||||||\n|-\n|13 ||||||||||||||||\n|-\n|14 ||||||||||||||||\n|-\n|15 ||||||||||||||||\n|-\n|16 ||||||||||||||||\n|-\n|17 ||||||||||||||||\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\nSource: [http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/asistencia Liga MX Femenil]\n\n=== Liguilla ===\nThe eigh best teams play two games against each other on a home-and-away basis. The higher seeded teams play on their home field during the second leg. The winner of each match up is determined by [[Two-legged tie#Tiebreaking|aggregate score]]. In the quarterfinals and semifinals, if the two teams are tied on aggregate and on [[Away goals rule|away goals]], the higher seeded team advances.<ref>per Liga MX Femenil online 'reglamentos' 2019/2020 (QF and SF) - \"De existir empate en el n\u00famero de goles, la posici\u00f3n se definir\u00e1 a favor del Club que haya anotado una mayor cantidad de goles actuando como visitante.\"</ref> In the final, if the two teams are tied after both legs, the match goes to extra time and, if necessary, a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]].\n\n<!--\n{{8TeamBracket-2Leg \n| RD1=[[#Quarter-finals|Quarter-finals]]\n| RD2=[[#Semi-finals|Semi-finals]]\n| RD3=[[#Final|Final]]\n| group1=\n| group2=\n| group3=\n\n| seed-width=\n| team-width=\n| game-score-width=\n| agg-score-width=\n\n| RD1-seed01=1\n| RD1-team01=\n| RD1-score01-1=\n| RD1-score01-2=\n| RD1-score01-agg=\n| RD1-seed02=2\n| RD1-team02=\n| RD1-score02-1=\n| RD1-score02-2=\n| RD1-score02-agg=\n| RD1-seed03=3\n| RD1-team03=\n| RD1-score03-1=\n| RD1-score03-2=\n| RD1-score03-agg=\n| RD1-seed04=4\n| RD1-team04=\n| RD1-score04-1=\n| RD1-score04-2=\n| RD1-score04-agg=\n| RD1-seed05=5\n| RD1-team05=\n| RD1-score05-1=\n| RD1-score05-2=\n| RD1-score0