ijuana (women)|Tijuana]] vs [[Santos Laguna (women)|Santos Laguna]]<br>{{small|(22 August 2019)}}<br>'''Clausura:'''175<br>[[Club Le\u00f3n (women)|Le\u00f3n]] vs [[Deportivo Toluca F.C. (women)|Toluca]]<br>{{small|(3 February 2020)}}\n|attendance\t\t= '''Apertura:'''380,355<br>'''Clausura:'''172,959\n|average attendance\t= '''Apertura:'''2,224<br> '''Clausura:''' 2,189\n|prevseason=[[2018\u201319 Liga MX Femenil season|2018\u201319]]\n|nextseason=''[[2020\u201321 Liga MX Femenil season|2020\u201321]]''\n|extra information=Stats are from the regular season only\n}}\n\nThe '''2019\u201320 [[Liga MX Femenil]] season''' is the third season of the top-flight women's football league in Mexico. The season was contested by nineteen teams, all being the counterpart women's teams of the men's league clubs [[Liga MX]]. The season was split into two championships\u2014the [[#Torneo Apertura|Torneo Apertura]] and the [[#Torneo Clausura|Torneo Clausura]]\u2014each in an identical format and each contested by the same nineteen teams. Unlike the two previous editions. As of this season, the participating teams will face each other instead of being divided into two groups.<ref name=\"LMFMT\">{{cite web |last1=D\u00edaz L\u00f3pez |first1=Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s |title=Liga MX Femenil tambi\u00e9n tendr\u00e1 nuevo formato, sin Grupos y otro l\u00edmite de edad |url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/liga-mx-femenil/liga-mx-femenil-cambios-reglamento-apertura-2019 |website=mediotiempo |accessdate=12 July 2019 |date=20 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Teams, stadiums, and personnel==\nThe following nineteen teams competed this season. [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]] and [[FC Ju\u00e1rez]] are fielding a team for the first time.\n\n===Stadiums and locations===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! [[Club Am\u00e9rica (women)|Am\u00e9rica]]\n! [[Club Atlas (women)|Atlas]]\n! [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis (women)|Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]]\n! [[Cruz Azul (women)|Cruz Azul]]\n! [[C.D. Guadalajara (women)|Guadalajara]]\n|-\n| [[Estadio Azteca]]\n| [[Estadio Jalisco]]\n| [[Estadio Alfonso Lastras]]\n| [[Estadio 10 de Diciembre]]\n| [[Estadio Akron]]\n|-\n| Capacity: '''81,070'''\n| Capacity: '''55,110'''\n| Capacity: '''25,111'''\n| Capacity: '''14,500'''\n| Capacity: '''46,232'''\n|-\n| [[File:Estadio Azteca, 2015.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Vista del estadio jalisco.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Estadio-alfonso-lastras9.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Inside of Estadio 10 de Diciembre.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Omnilife Stadium.png|150px]]\n|-\n! [[FC Ju\u00e1rez (women)|Ju\u00e1rez]]\n! [[Club Le\u00f3n (women)|Le\u00f3n]]\n! [[C.F. Monterrey (women)|Monterrey]]\n! [[Monarcas Morelia (women)|Morelia]]\n! [[Club Necaxa (women)|Necaxa]]\n|-\n| [[Estadio Ol\u00edmpico Benito Ju\u00e1rez]]\n| [[Estadio Le\u00f3n]]\n| [[Estadio BBVA]]\n| [[Estadio Morelos]]\n| [[Estadio Victoria]]\n|-\n| Capacity: '''19,703'''\n| Capacity: '''31,297'''\n| Capacity: '''51,348'''\n| Capacity: '''34,795'''\n| Capacity: '''23,851'''\n|-\n| [[File:Panoramicaestadiobenitojuarez.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Estadio Le\u00f3n (Nou Camp), Le\u00f3n, Guanajuato, M\u00e9xico -Imagen Actual- 2013-12-10 14-09.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Estadio BBVA Bancomer Inauguration.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Estadio Morelos.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Estadio Victoria (Aguascalientes).jpg|150px]]\n|-\n! [[C.F. Pachuca (women)|Pachuca]]\n! [[Club Puebla (women)|Puebla]]\n! [[Quer\u00e9taro F.C. (women)|Quer\u00e9taro]]\n! [[Santos Laguna (women)|Santos Laguna]]\n! [[Club Tijuana (women)|Tijuana]]\n|-\n| [[Estadio Hidalgo]]\n| [[Estadio Cuauht\u00e9moc]]\n| [[Estadio Corregidora]]\n| [[Estadio Corona]]\n| [[Estadio Caliente]]\n|-\n| Capacity: '''27,512'''\n| Capacity: '''51,726'''\n| Capacity: '''33,162'''\n| Capacity: '''29,237'''\n| Capacity: '''27,333'''\n|-\n| [[File:Estadio Hidalgo Huracan.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Rampa norte.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Estadio la Corregidora.JPG|150px]]\n| [[File:Estadio Corona TSM.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Xolos estadio caliente.jpg|150px]]\n|-\n! [[Deportivo Toluca F.C. (women)|Toluca]]\n! [[Tigres UANL (women)|UANL]]\n! [[Club Universidad Nacional (women)|UNAM]]\n|-\n| [[Estadio Nemesio D\u00edez]]\n| [[Estadio Universitario (UANL)|Estadio Universitario]]\n| La Cantera\n|-\n| Capacity: '''31,000'''\n| Capacity: '''41,886'''\n| Capacity: '''2,000'''\n|-\n| [[File:Diablos 05.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:Estadio Universitario UANL.jpg|150px]]\n|\n|}\n\n===Alternate venues===\n* Am\u00e9rica \u2013 Cancha Centenario No. 5<ref>http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/estadio/1421/estadio-cancha-centenario-no-5-natural-instalaciones-club-america</ref>\n* Atlas \u2013 Estadio Colomos Alfredo 'Pistache' Torres (Capacity: 3,000)<ref>http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/estadio/109/estadio-colomos-alfredo-pistache-torres</ref>\n* Guadalajara \u2013 Verde Valle<ref>http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/estadio/36/estadio-verde-valle</ref>\n* Monterrey \u2013 El Barrial (Capacity: 570)<ref>http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/estadio/675/estadio-el-barrial</ref>\n* UANL \u2013 Instalaciones Zuazua (Capacity: 800)<ref>http://www.ligafemenil.mx/cancha/estadio/34/estadio-instalaciones-zuazua</ref>\n\n{{Location map+ |Mexico |width=800 |float=center|caption=Location of the 2019\u201320 Liga MX Femenil teams|places=\n{{Location map~ |Mexico |lat=20.666667|long=-103.35    |label=[[C.D. Guadalajara (women)|Guadalajara]]<br>[[Club Atlas (women)|Atlas]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Mexico |lat=21.116667|long=-101.683333|label=[[Club Le\u00f3n (women)|Le\u00f3n]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Mexico |lat=31.752456|long=-106.469965|label=[[FC Ju\u00e1rez (women)|Ju\u00e1rez]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Mexico |lat=25.666667|long=-100.3     |label=[[Tigres UANL (women)|UANL]]<br>[[C.F. Monterrey (women)|Monterrey]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Mexico |lat=19.768333|long=-101.189444|label=[[Monarcas Morelia (women)|Morelia]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Mexico |lat=21.876   |long=-102.296   |label=