d GAA engine|Ford GAA V12]]'''\n* 1999 - Current '''[[Ford Duratec V6 engine#5.9 L V12|Aston Martin 6.0L V12]]''' (Originally made by Aston Martin under Ford ownership, continued by Aston Martin to present day.)\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Ford cars]]\n* [[List of Ford platforms]]\n* [[List of Ford bellhousing patterns]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.302w.com/ Website & Forums dedicated to the Ford Windsor Engine]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050518000641/http://www.fordclassics.com/enginespecs.html Specs on Ford overhead valve V8 engines]\n\n{{Ford Motor Company}}\n{{Ford v8 engines}}\n{{Ford modern v8 engines}}\n\n[[Category:Ford engines| ]]\n[[Category:Ford Motor Company|Engines]]\n[[Category:Lists of engines|Ford]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n'''[[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] engines''' are those used in Ford [[automobile|vehicles]] and in aftermarket, sports and kit applications. Different engine ranges are used in various global navistar markets.\n\n==[[3 cylinder engines]]==\n* 2012\u2013present '''[[Ford EcoBoost engine#EcoBoost I-3|1.0 L EcoBoost I-3]]'''\n* 2017\u2013present 1.1 L Duratec Ti-VCT I-3, naturally-aspirated \n* 2017\u2013present 1.2 L & 1.5 L Ti-VCT I-3, naturally-aspirated \"Dragon\" <ref>https://www.team-bhp.com/news/ford-debut-dragon-12l-petrol-engine-figo-crossover</ref>\n* 2018\u2013present '''[[Ford EcoBoost engine#1.5-L Dragon|1.5 L EcoBoost I-3]]'''\n\n==4 cylinder==\n* 1908&ndash;1927 '''[[Ford Model T engine]]'''\n* 1928&ndash;1931 '''Ford Model A engine''' ''(see [[Ford Model A (1927-1931)]])''\n* 1932&ndash;1934 '''Ford Model B engine''' ''(see [[Ford Model B (1932)]])''\n* 1932&ndash;1962 '''[[Ford Sidevalve]]'''\n* 1951&ndash;1966 '''[[Ford Zephyr engine|Consul 4]]'''&mdash;([[United Kingdom]])\n* 1961&ndash;1977 '''[[Ford Essex V4 engine|Essex V4]]'''&mdash;([[United Kingdom]]: Used in [[Ford Transit|Transit Mk.1]], [[Ford Granada (Europe)|Granada Mk.1/C